               <p>CHARLES EARITH. I am a <rs id="t18310407-249-viclabel1336" type="occupation">silk-dyer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310407-249-victim1729 t18310407-249-viclabel1336"></join>, and live in Goswell-street. The prisoner was in my employ a fortnight; I missed some articles, and in consequence of information, I gave him into custody - I have since seen four shawls, worth a guinea each, at a pawnbroker's - I missed one on the 17th of March, and one on the 19th.</p>
